## Implementation Details

The Analytics component is correctly placed in the App component:
```typescript
import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";

const App = () => {
  return (
    <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>
      <TooltipProvider>
        {/* ... other components ... */}
        <Analytics />
      </TooltipProvider>
    </QueryClientProvider>
  );
};
```

This implementation:
- Uses the correct import path for React/Vite (`@vercel/analytics/react`)
- Places the component at the appropriate location in the component tree
- Follows the official Vercel documentation exactly as specified in the quickstart guide

## Next Steps for User

To enable Web Analytics in production:
1. Ensure the project is deployed to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project Settings → Analytics)
3. Deploy the application
4. Verify tracking by checking the browser Network tab for requests to Vercel analytics endpoints
5. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard

